Mini Project 6 : Palindrome Checker using Recursion 
Palindrome Checker using Recursion in Python 

2. Problem Statement 
To design and implement a program that checks whether a given string is a palindrome using 
recursion. The program should take user input and determine if the string reads the same 
forward and backward. 

3. Objective 
• To understand recursion in Python 
• To check palindrome using recursive logic 
• To replace loops using recursion 
• To improve logical thinking skills 
• To implement string processing 

4.Tools Used 
• Python 3 
• VS Code / IDLE 

5.Description 
This project implements a Palindrome Checker using recursion. A palindrome is a word, 
phrase, or number that reads the same forward and backward (e.g., madam, level). 
The program uses recursion to compare the first and last characters of the string. If they match, 
the function calls itself with the remaining substring. This continues until the base condition is 
met. 

6.Algorithm 
 
       • Start the program 
       • Input a string 
       • Define recursive function 
       • Compare first and last characters 
       • If equal → call function again 
       • If not equal → return False 
       • If string length ≤ 1 → return True 
       • Display result 
       • End program             
 
7.Program (Python Code) 
 
  def is_palindrome(s): 
    # Base condition 
    if len(s) <= 1: 
        return True 
     
    # Check first and last character 
    if s[0] != s[-1]: 
        return False 
     
    # Recursive call 
    return is_palindrome(s[1:-1]) 
 
# Main program 
text = input("Enter a string: ") 
 
# Convert to lowercase (optional) 
text = text.lower() 
 
if is_palindrome(text): 
    print("It is a Palindrome") 
else: 
    print("Not a Palindrome")

